	<Title>
		Wilson&apos;s syndrome: An accepted medical diagnosis?
	</Title>
	<Abstract>
		The existence of Wilson&apos;s syndrome &amp;mdash; often described as mild or subclinical hypothyroidism &amp;mdash; is controversial.
	</Abstract>
	<Question>
		Is Wilson&apos;s syndrome a legitimate ailment?
	</Question>
